==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amylene
<hw>Am"y*lene</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>One of a group of metameric hydrocarbons, <chform>C5H10</chform>,
of the ethylene series. The colorless, volatile, mobile liquid commonly
called amylene is a mixture of different members of the group.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amylic</ent>⟦br⟧
